<h1>Augmented Reality: Interaction</h1>
<h2>Floorplan Model</h2>
<p>
  To measure the accuracy of my 3D modeling software, I imported and rendered a virtual model onto the walls of
  my apartment's kitchen and living room. Using pan gestures, I then arranged and scaled the model accordingly 
  to match the dimensions of my apartment in the world space. While the model effectively covered the world space, 
  it left a lot to be desired in terms of precision and alignment. Future iterations should explore image tracking in 
  addition to world tracking, aiming for a more realistic virtual model that convincingly snaps to the room walls in view.
</p>
